We have reported on the discovery of continuously
polar and superconducting phases in STO which can explain a range of phenomena: from the dome of the
superconducting critical temperature, to ruling out some roles of defects, and the pseudogap behavior.
We observe a sharply rising (divergent-like) superconducting critical temperature projecting no apparent
cap on the critical temperature of STO as it is tuned towards the polar quantum phase transition.
